cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1) cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the capacity region of a bi-directional relay channel and derives inner and outer bounds on the achievable rate regions. 
2) cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of relays to facilitate communication between multiple terminal nodes and a base station. 
3) cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper considers user cooperation and the use of overheard and own-message side information to improve network performance. 
4) cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed protocols in Gaussian noise, which is relevant to multimedia communication. 
5) cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the paper proposes new temporal protocols that combine network coding, random binning, and user cooperation to improve network performance.
